First off, the bagels are great. They genuinely come close to new York bagels. HOWEVER, everything they put on it does not! I ordered two things to see if it was a genuine place. First the everything bagel with regular cream cheese. The cream cheese was not as good as the cream cheese authentic places use it tasted very cheap and there was barely any on it. In real NY bagel shops there is usually a 1/2 inch thick layer of cream cheese. Next, the bacon egg and cheese (no pork roll!!! So right off the bat, not real NY place). The bacon and egg was premade!! They had it in a container! It also tasted microwaved (I took off a star for this). It was so disgusting! REAL NY places cook the eggs and bacon to order!  So, a good place to buy decent bagels, but get them to go and put better stuff on it.

Very disappointing experience. I moved down from N.Y. a year ago. My wife and I always did a 25 mile round trip to Brueggers on the weekend because we liked it so much. When we moved down to Clearwater Florida, we were excited to learn there was a Brueggers in Tampa, yes I know its a long drive. I called in advance to ask for light colored bagels, did this in N.Y. as well. The person on the phone wouldn't make light colored bagels for us but said I could pick the lightest colored ones that I saw. When I got there I ordered a dozen and a half bagels. I needed 13 plain and they didn't have enough. I also needed 6 salt and they didn't have enough of them either, never apologize once. Then I ordered a bagel with bacon and egg only. When I got to the car it was egg with sausage. I came back to the store and the apathetic man said he ask me if I wanted sausage and egg, which he never did. Then he said I said meat only, which I never did. The whole time he had an obvious attitude. Needless to say we won't be making that trip from Clearwater again. Very disappointed!!!!!
